text: SeaTac is a city in southern King County, Washington, United States. It is a suburb of Seattle, Washington. The name SeaTac is a combination of Seattle and Tacoma. It is named from the Seattleâ€“Tacoma International Airport. The city of SeaTac is in area and has a population of 31,454 according to the 2020 census. Residents voted for incorporation on March 14, 1989, and the city incorporated in February 1990. ==References== Category:Cities in Washington (state)
